            <div class="hero-small-line"></div>
            <p>Lay your best fitting pants flat on the ground and measure straight across the belt line.&nbsp;&nbsp;Double this measurement to get your true size.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;There's usually about a 2"&nbsp;disparity from your true size to your tagged size.</p><br />
            <h5 class="project-tittle">Inseam</h5>
            <div class="hero-small-line"></div>
            <p>Measure from the top of the belt line and follow the outside leg all the way to the bottom of your pants.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is usually minimal disparity between your tagged size versus true size with your inseam.</p><br />
